The paper deals with compressed sensing and signal processing, which are core topics in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The use of weighted $\ell_1$-minimization is a machine learning technique, which falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of probability theory and statistical inference, which are relevant to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with exploiting extra structure in the signal, which is a topic in the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
